  "texts": [
    "All models were trained under 4-bit quantization for a single epoch.",
    "Despite the strong convergence observed in smaller models, the LLaMA-2-13B run on UltraChat shows relatively higher final training loss (1.289) and evaluation loss (1.317).",
    "This is primarily due to underfitting of the DRaFT-1 adapter, as the model was fine-tuned for only 800 steps under constrained resource conditions.",
    "Nonetheless, these results demonstrate that DRaFT-Q remains stable and functional at scale, and with extended training, it can further optimize larger models like LLaMA-2-13B.",
    "This underscores the method's potential for scalable, memory-efficient fine-tuning of even larger language models."
